Void Harvester

Brought to you by Ad Free and Free

Product notes

A simple idle game.  
Modern idle games run stuff in the background of your phone for third party analytics or whatever.  
This does not; instead it calculates what you collected based on the current time and the time of the last save.
It runs in airplane mode.

It creates a save file to load from.

Play:

Start in the Sol solar system and collect resources to your mothership by harvester ships, 
harvester ships are autonomous vehicles that bounce back and forth between resource objectives and the ship
mining resources is instantaneous, but the amount of resources obtained can be upgraded
resource nodes include planets, celestial bodies, asteroid belts, larger individual asteroids, the star, and possibly more like a static space dust collector
later in the game phase to different points in the galaxy
build outposts to collect resources and beam them to your ship anywhere in the galaxy
resources include iron, gold, platinum, plasma, etc.

research trees for how your ships operate, how resources are utilized and processed, items made to improve ships, etc.
Trade with planetary colonies and NPC ships can be achieved by getting into local beam range(fairly close)

menu
joystick moves your ship around, 
tap on a planet to navigate your ship to it/chase it as it orbits
tabs include resource intake and stockpile, crafted alloys, crafted items, ship upgrades, colony/NPC trading, and tools.




